content: When compiling rustc on my machine, it compiles and runs fine. However, when github checks the pull request, there is a compiler error saying that Place doesn't implement Display, and it points to a variable that is supposedly of type Place. However, the variable should be of type Symbol instead. https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/81158/checks?check_run_id=1720743811
@Kevin Tran github rebases PRs before testing them. You may have a semantic conflict, try rebasing over master.
